        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>LOS AN­GE­LES • Tommy Lasorda, the Los An­ge­les Dodgers’ colour­ful and can­tan­ker­ous long-time man­ager who led the team to four Na­tional League pen­nants and two World Se­ries cham­pi­onships in the 1970s and 1980s, has died. He was 93.</p>
    <p>Lasorda, who spent more than 70 years in the Dodgers or­gan­i­sa­tion, suf­fered a sud­den car­diopul­monary ar­rest at home on Thurs­day night and was taken to hos­pi­tal where he was pro­nounced dead a short time later, the base­ball team said in a state­ment on Fri­day.</p>


